08/03/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Negotiations on sealing a Stabilisation and Association Agreement (SAA) between the EU and BiH could start this summer, EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn confirmed in a statement for Radio Free Europe on Monday (7 March). 
While praising the country's progress in fulfilling the requirements in the EU Feasibility Study, Rehn also emphasised the need to restructure the police sector and co-operate fully with the UN war crimes tribunal.
Also Monday, Danish Parliament Speaker Christian Mejdahl met with members of the BiH presidency in Sarajevo. 
He voiced his country's full support for efforts by BiH to join the Euro-Atlantic structures. 
He also stressed the importance of full co-operation with The Hague tribunal. 
(Dnevni avaz - 08/03/05; Fena, NTV Hayat - 07/03/05)
